trend_summary: 2000-2020 imagery shows steady infill: extra houses and small commercial blocks clustered along main roads, slight industrial park growth southeast, but extensive tree cover persists and even thickens in pockets. Overall land-use shifts from low-rise sprawl to greener, moderately built suburbia without major high-density redevelopment.
notable_changes: Industrial park enlarges along the southeastern highway corridor, adding several new warehouses.
New strip-commercial buildings and parking lots appear near the eastern arterial intersection.
Scattered residential infill fills former vacant or wooded lots across the centre and west.
Main highway/arterial shows widening and a new on-ramp, boosting connectivity.
Tree canopy expands in neighbourhood interiors and along waterways, increasing overall greenness.
